<section id="fh5co-testimonials">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12 section-heading text-center" style="margin-bottom: 0">
        <h2>What is Fullstaq Ruby?</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
        <p>Fullstaq Ruby is an MRI-based Ruby distribution that's optimized for server production use cases. It is compiled with the <a href="https://medium.com/rubyinside/how-we-halved-our-memory-consumption-in-rails-with-jemalloc-86afa4e54aa3">Jemalloc</a> and <a href="https://www.joyfulbikeshedding.com/blog/2019-03-14-what-causes-ruby-memory-bloat.html">malloc_trim</a> patches, allowing lower memory usage and higher performance.</p>
        <p>We supplies binaries (DEBs, RPMs) so that you don't have to compile Ruby from source, and so that you can easily keep Ruby security-patched.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-1">
        <h3>Learn more</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-server-edition#why-was-fullstaq-ruby-created">Why did we make Fullstaq Ruby?</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-server-edition#how-it-works">How does it work?</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-server-edition#comparisons-to-other-systems">Comparisons to other systems</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-server-edition#faq">Frequently Asked Questions</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin: 1rem 0">-or-</p>
        <p><%= link_to 'Get Started', 'https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-server-edition#installation', class: 'btn btn-primary' %></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" style="margin-top: 3rem">
      <div class="col-md-5 col-md-offset-1">
        <h3>For the community, by the community</h3>
        <p>
          We intend for Fullstaq Ruby to be a true <em>community project</em>, welcoming contributors all over the world, and maintainable by anyone. To make this work, we are working on a lot more developer and contributor documentation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <h3>More improvements on the way</h3>
        <p>
          Fullstaq Ruby is in beta: it is a <strong>work-in-progress</strong>. For example, we have DEBs/RPMs, but <em>no APT/YUM repository yet</em>. Further memory reduction optimizations are possible. And much more.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-12 text-center">
        <p class="lead">So stay tuned, folks!</p>
        <p>
          <%= link_to 'View our roadmap', 'https://github.com/fullstaq-labs/fullstaq-ruby-umbrella/projects' %><br>
          <a href="https://twitter.com/honglilai">Follow Twitter for news</a>
        </p>
      </div>
